00:50:04,481 --> 00:50:06,106
Yes, sir?

644
00:50:06,209 --> 00:50:08,118
Could you come with me,
please?

645
00:50:08,225 --> 00:50:10,265
Sure.
Can Ed come too?

646
00:50:10,368 --> 00:50:11,775
Mister...

647
00:50:12,353 --> 00:50:15,135
Crane.
Ed Crane.

648
00:50:15,233 --> 00:50:17,982
You also have an interest
in the securing porperty?

649
00:50:19,393 --> 00:50:20,953
He's a barber.

650
00:50:21,024 --> 00:50:24,439
- Second chair.
- Not an owner.

651
00:50:24,545 --> 00:50:28,320
No, he's, uh, family.
He's my brother-in-law.

652
00:50:28,416 --> 00:50:31,515
It would be best
if he waited here.

653
00:51:07,904 --> 00:51:09,660
The barber shop.

654
00:51:13,505 --> 00:51:17,334
Doris and Frank's father had worked
30 years to own it free and clear.

655
00:51:17,441 --> 00:51:21,303
Now it got signed over to the bank,
and the bank signed some over to Frank.

656
00:51:21,408 --> 00:51:24,704
And Frank signed the money
to Freddy Riedenschneider.

657
00:51:24,800 --> 00:51:26,840
Who got into town
two days later...

658
00:51:26,945 --> 00:51:29,694
And told me to meet him
at Da Vinci's for lunch.

659
00:51:32,289 --> 00:51:34,710
Not fried, poached.
Three of 'em for two minutes.

660
00:51:34,817 --> 00:51:37,686
Strip steak, medium rare,
flapjacks, potatoes, tomato juice...

661
00:51:37,792 --> 00:51:39,069
And plenty of hot coffee.

662
00:51:40,064 --> 00:51:42,552
- You have any Prairie Oysters?
- No, sir.

663
00:51:42,624 --> 00:51:45,658
Then bring me a fruit cocktail
while I wait.

664
00:51:47,969 --> 00:51:49,911
- You're Crane?
- Yeah.

665
00:51:50,016 --> 00:51:51,511
Barber, right?

666
00:51:51,616 --> 00:51:53,405
I'm Freddy Riedenschneider.
Hungry?

667
00:51:53,504 --> 00:51:54,715
Uh, not really.

668
00:51:54,785 --> 00:51:57,502
They tell me the chow's okay here.
I made some inquiries.

669
00:51:58,912 --> 00:52:01,880
Look, I don't want to waste your time,
so I'll eat while we talk.

670
00:52:02,017 --> 00:52:03,097
Do you mind?
You don't mind.

671
00:52:03,200 --> 00:52:05,950
While I'm in town
I'm staying at the Hotel Metropole.

672
00:52:06,016 --> 00:52:09,846
Turandot Suite. Yeah, it's goofy.
They named their suites after operas.

673
00:52:09,952 --> 00:52:11,807
